Based on the search results, here's what I found about the JetBrains Ring UI library:

Ring UI is a collection of JetBrains Web UI components. For basic Button usage, you can import and use it like this:

```javascript
import '@jetbrains/ring-ui-built/components/style.css';
import Button from '@jetbrains/ring-ui-built/components/button/button';

export const Demo = () => {
  return (
    <Button onClick={() => alertService.successMessage('Hello world')}>
      Click me
    </Button>
  );
};
```


For icons specifically, SVG icons can be imported directly as React components and they pass props to the Icon component:

```javascript
// Before (and still fully supported)
import pencilIcon from '@jetbrains/icons/pencil.svg'
import Icon from '@jetbrains/components/icon/icon'
<Icon glyph={pencilIcon} size={Icon.Size.Size12} title="edit" />

// After
import PencilIcon from '@jetbrains/icons/pencil.svg'
<PencilIcon size={PencilIcon.Size.Size12} title="edit" />
```


Note: The `size`, `width` and `height` props are deprecated in the Icon component. The intrinsic size of the icon (width and height SVG attributes) is used instead.

For more detailed Button component documentation with the `icon` prop specifically, I'd recommend checking:
- The Ring UI Storybook documentation at https://jetbrains.github.io/ring-ui/develop-storybook/
- The GitHub repository at https://github.com/JetBrains/ring-ui

